<head><title>Internet Pinball Machine Database: Bally 'Bally Derby'</title>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="imagetoolbar" CONTENT="no">
<meta name="keywords" content="IPD IPDB Internet Pinball Machine Database Game Bally Bally Derby One Ball Game Incorporates 'Odds and Payout' units. It dispenses 5 cent coins when a skill shot is made into a hole on the playfield, the amount depending on the current odds. There is an electric motor that drives the payout unit. The odds drum coil is activated when the ball rolls over a leaf switch beneath the playfield. There is a mechanical timer (similar to a wind up watch) that will run out after about 10 minutes. The timer has a lever which activates a continuity switch. The game originally ran on batteries, but many were converted to run on power outlets via a 110VAC/12VDC transformer. Advertised as 50 inches long by 24 inches wide.  Bon MacDougall ">
